This paper deals with algorithmic frameworks for personalization and bias control, which are topics that fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential societal impact of personalization methods, which could be relevant to the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper proposes a constrained optimization problem, which could be relevant to the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or cryptography and security (cs.CR).
